    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_852399212" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/852399212" />
    <a title="Sumant" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/21982745-sumant"><img alt="Sumant" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1373196404p2/21982745.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/852399212?book_show_action=true">Feb 11, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Sumant" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Sumant" href="/user/show/21982745-sumant">Sumant</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audio CD 9781593979768" href="/book/show/830980.A_Crown_of_Swords">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21982745-sumant?shelf=whell-of-time">whell-of-time</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/21982745-sumant?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer852399212" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5252264524815251154"><b>Re-read update</b><br/>--------------------------<br/><b>Re-Read Groups</b> : <br/><br/><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/topic/group_folder/299599?group_id=99675' rel='nofollow noopener'>Not a book club</a><br/><br/><a href='https://www.goodreads.com/topic/group_folder/292487?group_id=148164' rel='nofollow noopener'>Buddies,Books &amp; Baubles</a><br/><br/>--------------------------<br/><br/>I am going to repeat myself in this review due to the fact that I am really enjoying this series in audio rather than on paper. The credit of which must be given to the narrators of these audio books who are <b>Michael Kramer</b> and <b>Kate Reading</b>. I especially like how they are able to enact so many different characters in this book.<br/><br/>In this book we have major pov&apos;s from <b>Mat</b> &amp; <b>Rand</b>. W</span>
  <span id="freeText5252264524815251154" style="display:none"><b>Re-read update</b><br />--------------------------<br /><b>Re-Read Groups</b> : <br /><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/topic/group_folder/299599?group_id=99675" rel="nofollow noopener">Not a book club</a><br /><br /><a href="https://www.goodreads.com/topic/group_folder/292487?group_id=148164" rel="nofollow noopener">Buddies,Books &amp; Baubles</a><br /><br />--------------------------<br /><br />I am going to repeat myself in this review due to the fact that I am really enjoying this series in audio rather than on paper. The credit of which must be given to the narrators of these audio books who are <b>Michael Kramer</b> and <b>Kate Reading</b>. I especially like how they are able to enact so many different characters in this book.<br /><br />In this book we have major pov's from <b>Mat</b> &amp; <b>Rand</b>. We also get pov's from the forsaken and the shaido. I am really surprised by the fact that book ends on a major cliffhanger for one of the most important characters in the series. All the previous books <b>Jordan</b> has been able to tie up the plot in that book while adding to the ongoing story, but this end definitely surprised me and left me wanting more.<br /><br />There is a large infestation of forsaken, dark friends and dark things in this book especially in <b>Ebou Dar</b>. All of these make the story more richer, it's not like someone has been added to the story for the heck of it. <br /><br />I think <b>Jordan</b> has already introduced to us the good guys of the story and now he is adding the bad guys to the story.<br /><br />Although these are the good parts, but my major complaint continues with the story with how cribby the female characters are presented in the story, they just keep on complaining about everyone and everything. Also the guys keep thinking the other guy knows women better than him. <br /><br />If only <b>Jordan</b> had been able to remove these annoying part from a such a rich world and story, I would have doubly enjoyed this book.<br /><br />I am going to bump up my rating and gonna give 4/5 stars.<br /><br />--------------------------<br /><i>Crown of swords</i> was a mixed bag book for me, because although the book dragged a lot in the middle but the ending of the book was superb. Also <i>Rand</i> finally doing something was itself refreshing to read. But I have to admit the series has really started bogging down from the last book, and although sometimes I really got frustrated while reading the book but I am going to continue with the series as <i>Sanderson</i> has ended it.<br /><br />Some of the strong points of the book were<br /><br /><i>Rand's pov.</i><br /><i>Rand taking strong decisions.</i><br /><i>Children of light story.</i><br /><br />Some of the weak points of book are<br /><br /><i>Elayne &amp; Nyaneve's search for bowl of wind.</i><br /><i>Too many Aes sedai.</i><br /><br />Let me elaborate on the above points further<br /><br /><i>Rand's pov.</i><br /><br />As we knew from the last book that the current amrylin had hatched an conspiracy by which she will be able to kidnap <i>Rand</i>, and bring him to the tower so that she can control him. But all hell breaks loose at <i>Dumai wells</i> where in the <i>shaido aiel</i> get involved in order to capture <i>Rand</i> from the aes sedai, and involved in this mix are <i>Rand's Aashman</i> who attack in order to rescue <i>Rand</i>. <i>Rand</i> manages to free himself and gives the aes sedai to the wise ones. I think this book focuses a lot on <i>Rand</i> he keeps on hearing voice of <i>Lewis therin</i> who asks him to kill any man who can channel.<br /><br /><i>Rand taking strong decisions.</i><br /><br /><b>Rand thrust his hands high and channeled. “I am the Dragon Reborn!” The words boomed across the square, amplified by Air and Fire, and flames shot up from his hands a hundred feet. Behind him, the Asha’man filled the sky with balls of fire streaking in every direction. All save Dashiva, who made blue lightnings crackle in a jagged web above the square. No more was needed.</b><br /><br />This was quite interesting reading because he finally decides to tie the bell around cat's neck in the sense that he tackles the politics in <i>Carihien</i> when he comes to know that power has been seized by <i>Colavere</i>. He also confronts the sea folk and makes a deal with them, and finally he decides to attack <i>Illian</i> which has <i>Sammel</i> holed up in it. <i>Jordan</i> really writes some awesome battle scenes in this book and there is no doubt that he is in complete control of his prose.<br /><br /><i>Children of light story.</i><br /><br />This story has been developing a lot from the previous book where in the children of light have the queen of andor as prisoner with them. At the start of the book some unexpected things happen due to which <i>Morgese's</i> already complex situation becomes more complex. I would really like to read more about the children of the light as they seem like an interesting bunch to me. They are definitely less irritable than the aes sedai for sure.<br /><br />Now let me elaborate on the weaker points of the book<br /><br /><i>Elayne &amp; Nyaneve's search for bowl of wind.</i><br /><br />This has got to be for me the worst part of the series so far, because now <i>Elayne</i> seems to have joined obnoxious <i>Nyaneve</i>, they basically make life of poor <i>Mat</i> hell throughout the book. <i>Nyaneve</i> has got to be worst women character I have read in fantasy so far because all she wants to do is box someone's ear or force her decision on others, she really got on my nerves throughout the book and <i>Elyane</i> was not far behind her.<br /><br /><i>Too many Aes sedai.</i><br /><br />Man there are too many aes sedai in this book and to make matters worst we have a circle of run aways from tower in <i>Ebu dar</i>, and it is so hard to distinguish one aes sedai from other, if <i>Jordan</i> would not have given them names they all would have seemed like same person to me because they are so much like each other. They are similar to each other in a way that they just keep comparing each others strengths, and playing dirty politics with each other, and the worst part is the politics seems childish.<br /><br />Although the book definitely lagged in the middle, but as has always been the case with <i>Jordan</i> he is a great finisher and so he managed to keep me on the edge of the seat for last few 50 pages. I give this book 3/5 stars.</span>
  <a data-text-id="5252264524815251154" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


